fasper(double[], double[], int, double, double, double[], double[], int) - Static method in class danfulea.math.numerical.FFTAnalysis
Given n data points with abscissas x[1..n] (which need not be equally spaced) and ordinates y[1..n], and given a desired oversampling factor ofac (a typical value being 4 or larger), this routine fills array wk1[1..nwk] with a sequence of nout_fasper increasing frequencies (not angular frequencies) up to hifac times the “average” Nyquist frequency, and fills array wk2[1..nwk] with the values of the Lomb normalized periodogram at those frequencies.
